  "prompt": "Which optional subjects can I choose for the IAS exam?",
  "response": "In the Indian Administrative Services (IAS) exam, which is part of the Civil Services Examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC), candidates can choose from a range of optional subjects for the Mains examination. The following is a list of optional subjects available for the IAS exam:\n\n1. Anthropology\n2. Economics\n3. Geography\n4. History\n5. Law\n6. Political Science and International Relations\n7. Psychology\n8. Sociology\n9. Public Administration\n10. Philosophy\n11. Mathematics\n12. Botany\n13. Chemistry\n14. Physics\n15. Zoology\n16. Literature (several languages including Hindi, English, Tamil, Urdu, etc.)\n17. Agriculture\n18. Forestry\n19. Animal Husbandry and Veterinary Science\n20. Medical Science\n21. Management\n22. Statistics\n23. Commerce and Accountancy\n24. History of Art\n\nCandidates should choose an optional subject based on their interest, background, and familiarity, as this can significantly impact their performance in the examination. It is also advisable to check the latest UPSC notification or website for any updates or changes in the list of optional subjects.",
